      "span_text": "In a study which assessed teeth with endodontic failures, 65% of the cases exhibited poor quality obturation, whereas 42% of the teeth had some canals which were left untreated. In another study, an association was found between increased incidence of periapical periodontitis and inadequate or overextended root fillings."
